  "prompt": "What are the best book in preparation for bank exams?",
  "response": "Preparing for bank exams requires a strategic approach and reliable resources. Here are some of the best books that can help you prepare effectively for bank exams:\n\n1. **Quantitative Aptitude:**\n   - \"Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\" by R.S. Aggarwal\n   - \"Fast Track Objective Arithmetic\" by Rajesh Verma\n\n2. **Reasoning Ability:**\n   - \"A Modern Approach to Verbal and Non-Verbal Reasoning\" by R.S. Aggarwal\n   - \"Analytical Reasoning\" by M.K. Pandey\n\n3. **English Language:**\n   - \"Objective General English\" by S.P. Bakshi\n   - \"Word Power Made Easy\" by Norman Lewis\n\n4. **General and Banking Awareness:**\n   - \"Banking Awareness\" by Arihant Experts\n   - \"Guide to Banking General Awareness\" by RPH Editorial Board\n\n5. **Computer Awareness:**\n   - \"Computer Awareness\" by Arihant Experts\n   - \"Objective Computer Awareness\" by R. Pillai\n\n6. **Previous Year Papers and Practice Sets:**\n   - \"Bank PO Solved Papers\" by Kiran Prakashan\n   - \"Bank PO Practice Test Papers\" by EduGorilla\n\n7. **General Knowledge:**\n   - \"Manorama Yearbook\" by Mammen Mathew\n   - \"Lucent\u2019s General Knowledge\"\n\n8. **Study Guide:**\n   - \"Comprehensive Guide to IBPS-CWE Bank PO/MT Preliminary & Main Exam\" by Disha Experts\n   - \"Bank PO/MT Exam - Complete Study Material\" by Arihant Experts\n\nMake sure to also stay updated with daily current affairs, and practice mock tests regularly. Consistent and thorough preparation using these resources can significantly enhance your chances of success in bank exams.",
